snippet: Astronomers say they have spotted a fifth moon orbiting Pluto, giving it more moons than Mercury, Venus, Earth and Mars combined and supplying science-minded wits with Twitter material.
abstract: Astronomers using the Hubble Space Telescope identify a fifth moon orbiting Pluto; discovery of moon, provisionally called P5, does not change the terms of the debate surrounding Pluto's planethood.
lead_paragraph: Astronomers say they have spotted a fifth moon orbiting Pluto, giving it more moons than Mercury, Venus, Earth and Mars combined and supplying science-minded wits with Twitter material.

headline.seo: Astronomers Spot Fifth Moon Orbiting Pluto
headline.main: Another Moon on Pluto Has Astronomers Aglow
